author: blair
msg: * tools/client-side/svn_load_dirs.pl
(determine_native_eol): Actually return what the subroutine is
supposed to, the native eol.  Rename native_eol and
native_eol_length to eol and eol_length respectively to avoid a
name clash with a global variable.
(main): Fix a bug where the native eol message was being printed
twice to standard out.  Do not print the native eol at all here,
leave that to determine_native_eol.

author: brane
msg: Clean up some of the mess in the Python tests by using the Sandbox class
instead of passing test names around and recalculating paths all over the
place.
[in subversion/tests/clients/cmdline]
* svntest/actions.py (make_repo_and_wc): Take a main.Sandbox parameter
instead of the test name, and use the paths stored there.
* svntest/main.py (Sandbox.build): Pass self to actions.make_repo_and_wc
instead of self.name.
* schedule_tests.py (add_files, add_directories, nested_adds,
delete_files, delete_dirs): Delete wrapper implementations. New
implementations renamed from add_files_core, add_directories_core,
nested_adds_core, delete_files_core, delete_dirs_core, respectively,
and changed to take just a main.Sandbox parameter and use the wc_path
stored there. All uses changed.
